Description: ClickFix is a social engineering technique where compromised legitimate sites lure users, often through browser update or 'Aw Snap!' error mimics. It uses pastejacking to inject malicious content into the clipboard, instructing users to paste it into a terminal. This delivers various malware, including droppers, downloaders, and malicious browser extensions.
